notes:
The following code was used to confirm jinja2 works with PyScript:

```
from jinja2 import Environment, DictLoader, select_autoescape

loader = DictLoader({
    "base.html": """
<html>
<head>
    <title>{% block title %}{% endblock %}
</head>
<body>
{% block content %}{% endblock %}
</body>
""",
    "index.html": """
{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block title %}Members{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
  <ul>
  {% for user in users %}
    <li><a href="{{ user.url }}">{{ user.username }}</a></li>
  {% endfor %}
  </ul>
{% endblock %}
""",
})
env = Environment(
    loader=loader,
    autoescape=select_autoescape()
)
template = env.get_template("index.html")
users = [
    {"url": "https://pyscript.net/", "username": "PyScript"},
    {"url": "https://anaconda.com/", "username": "Anaconda"},
    {"url": "https://pyodide.org/", "username": "Pyodide"},
    {"url": "https://micropython.org", "username": "MicroPython"}
]
print(template.render(users=users))
```
